  "prompt": "What on earth should I be instead of a fashionista if I'm an artist that draws?",
  "response": "If you're an artist who draws, you might consider embracing a title or identity that reflects your creative spirit and artistic focus. Here are a few ideas:\n\n1. **Visual Storyteller** - Emphasizes your ability to convey narratives through your art.\n2. **Illustrator** - A straightforward term that highlights your skill in creating visual interpretations.\n3. **Creative Designer** - If you venture into various design fields, this title can be inclusive.\n4. **Artistic Explorer** - Suggests a sense of discovery and experimentation in your work.\n5. **Sketch Artist** - Focuses on your drawings and captures the essence of your craft.\n6. **Painter of Imagination** - If you also work with painting, this suggests creativity and vision.\n7. **Art Enthusiast** - A more casual term that reflects your passion for art.\n8. **Visual Artist** - A broad title that encompasses various forms of visual expression.\n9. **Graphic Novelist** - If your work involves storytelling through sequential art.\n10. **Dream Weaver** - Evokes a sense of capturing dreams and ideas through your drawings.\n\nUltimately, choose a title that resonates with you and feels authentic to your artistic journey!",
